This took me exactly three hours. If you're an experienced baker, and know how to prep and multitask, this shouldn't take any more time (like I had started the buttercream while the meringue was baking). The buttercream set up beautifully, not one problem. Anyway, the cake itself is absolutely magnificent! Flavors are divine, and the combination perfect. While trimming it, I was able to sample everything, and what a yum! Some tips - prepare in advance: cut your parchment days prior, separate all the eggs at once in the beginning, toast the nuts while preheating the oven for the cake layer...doing things like this will greatly reduce your overall time. I also made some chocolate leaves for the top as a little decor.

