The cake is beautiful, but is a LOT of work. My cooking skills were no help at all, but my baking skills did. Like others, I made this over 2 days. The cake layers (BTW, since when are frosting layers counted, this is a SIX-layer cake!) were easy enough, but even with a stand mixer, that gorgeous buttercream was a pain. Our cool climate means proofing bread or making creme fraiche takes forever, but was perfect for making this buttercream. It cooled in less than half an hour, hastened by an ice bath. Assembly was easy, I shouldn't have worried about lining the layers up too much, they just get cut off, perfect for secret snacking later. But this was way too much work, although I will make it again if my husband requests it. I'll remind him about the 6 sticks of butter and the dozen and a half eggs, and that I used all the sugar I had in the house, but I'd endure it all again if a loved one requests it. Oh, and it definitely serves more than eight, and is too rich to be appreciated after a heavy meal.

Rating: 4
This is one of the best cakes I've made. It's restaurant quality and SUPER rich. I served it in literally 2 inch by 2 inch columns. Only alteration was to sub in a layer of chocolate hazelnut mousse (from another Epi recipe) for the middle buttercream because others said it was too rich and you don't have enough buttercream. Good addition. Couple tips: When cutting, don't go straight down from the top. Come in at an angle and use a sawing action with the sharpest knife you have. Spread your layers VERY even as they will bake almost exactly as you spread them and you want perfect rectangles. The sponge layer shrunk on me a bit. I made the entire cake with handbeaters. Totally possible although you'll need a glass of wine to calm yourself down when you think the buttercream will never come together. Took 15 min for me. Beat it with some ice below the bowl which helped. I made the mousse (my addition) and buttercreams the day before and then the cake layers the day of. Wrap the sides up with plastic wrap when chilling or transporting or storing. Would be GREAT served with a tart berry sauce or changing up some of the flavors in the layers to be chocolate and berries...for next time! Overall awesome showstopper!

