Rating: 4
Like previous reviews, my guests found this to be a hand down grand slam winner. Its so good that it became THE topic for one hour after dinner. Here are my notes. 1. Final amount is enough for 18-22 people. Its huge rich cake. 2. The first time I made this cake it took 5 hours--and re-did the butter creams. It could be done in 4 hours but you must have a great mixer and food processor. 3. Split prep of the layers and assembly over two days. I was burnt out after prepping the three layers and butter creams. 4. I cooked the cake layer too far and did not heed the directions close enough. Definitely pull the cake from the oven when just turning brown. 5. The buttercream will need to soften before assembly so remove it from the fridge early in the day. I found the microwaving the butter creams in 10 sec bursts softened them nicely.

