@erthywmn: the cocoa is used when making the souffle layers - it says to sift the cocoa over the souffle after it cools and before you cut it in half... :)

Rating: 4
I wish you could give two ratings-- one for instructions (i'ld give it a 2) and another for the finished product (I'd give it a 4). I agree with the previous reviewer who said that they said "never again" until they heard the responses of their guests. This was a very difficult recipe. The times listed were not accurate and I eneded up making the buttercream 3 times because I kept cooking it too long. Before doing it again, I think I would re-write the recipe instructions with times highlighted and then know that you should check the layers at half the recommended time. Definitely read and re-read the entire recipe so you can understand what you are up against before starting and give yourself a couple of days. The meringue layer was not hard but the cooking time, drying time realy adds up. Regarding the comments about the nuts, living in Texas we have lots of pecans. If I were doing it again, I would probably just use pecans since I always have them. I don't think it would affect the outcome. My husband is European and this is the sort of recipe that he grew up on so when I see things like this, I always try it. Completing the recipe was sort of like giving birth...labor was hard but it's a beautiful baby.

