Rating: 2
I made this cake for a Christmas party. The flavors and textures are very good. But it was fairly difficult.The recipes calls for 1T of unsweetened cocoa but never tells you when to add it. So I researched other souffle recipes to figure it out. I also have half sheet pans but, apparantly not all 1/2 sheet pans are the same size. Mine were 16x12 and the recipe call for 15x10. which I didn't relize till I went to cut the cakes in half. Yes, it's my fault, I should have checked the size of the pans before using them. My cake layers were a little thin, but the cake tasted great.

Rating: 4
This is what a cake consisting of 12 layers should be. The highlight of the concoction is the toasted hazelnut meringue. The cake was a time consuming endeavor, but it can be divided between two days. I made the layers (three kinds) in one day and then the frosting the next. I've never been a big fan of taking the time to do a meringue frosting (swiss, or whathaveyou), BUT this was worth the effort and would be delicious on a chocolate or exceptional vanilla white cake. I would make this again, but I would cut the pieces smaller. In fact, after a nice dinner, this would easily serve twice as many as the recipe indicates. If you are looking for something that looks professional but tastes homemade, this is the recipe for you. Oh yeah....just make sure you plan accordingly. Don't be like me and start baking the layers at 10:30 PM....